                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.452/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 24, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Department’s 22, February 2, 7 p.m. Before leaving Managua the Department
                    desires you to inform the Government that in your absence the Chargé d’Affaires,
                    as the representative of the United States, will take precedence over both the
                    Commander of the Special Service Squadron and the Brigade Commander. The Navy
                    Department has directed the Commander of the Special Service Squadron to be
                    guided accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
